            "textContents": [
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                    "paragraphTitle": "used to, would, get used to, be used to",
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "1. We use used to + base form to talk about finished habits and states: things that were true in the past but aren't true now."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "2. We can also use would + base form to talk about finished habits and routines, but not to talk about states."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "3. We use be used to to talk about something that was unfamiliar but is not unfamiliar now."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "4. We use get used to to talk about something that is still unfamiliar and not a current habit."
                    ]
                }
            ],
